WEBVTT

00:01.419 --> 00:03.086
<i>- Previously
on "Superman & Lois"...</i>

00:03.087 --> 00:06.340
Luthor's not gonna stop
until he destroys my life.

00:06.465 --> 00:07.799
<i>He even moved here
to make sure.</i>

00:07.800 --> 00:09.467
- This is my daughter,
Elizabeth.

00:09.468 --> 00:11.428
- We flipped
someone at the DOD.

00:11.429 --> 00:13.138
Turns out,
Elizabeth made contact.

00:13.139 --> 00:15.807
She was hoping not to be found.
- Where's Elizabeth now?

00:15.808 --> 00:18.143
- The only person
who knows that is Sam Lane.

00:18.144 --> 00:20.770
- He is without a heart.
- His body can heal itself.

00:20.771 --> 00:22.439
- He cannot create new organs.

00:22.440 --> 00:23.815
- Grandmom said
that we might be able

00:23.816 --> 00:25.316
to bring Dad back
if we can get his heart.

00:25.317 --> 00:26.443
- [groaning]

00:26.444 --> 00:28.153
[screams]

00:28.154 --> 00:29.654
- I wasn't ready.

00:29.655 --> 00:31.448
And now we can never
get him back.

00:31.449 --> 00:33.074
[sobbing]

00:33.075 --> 00:35.160
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:35.161 --> 00:38.163
<i>[somber music]</i>

00:38.164 --> 00:45.003
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:45.004 --> 00:47.756
<i>Can you ever truly explain</i>

00:47.757 --> 00:50.800
<i>how much a person
meant to you?</i>

00:50.801 --> 00:57.182
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:57.183 --> 00:59.476
<i>Is it even possible?</i>

00:59.477 --> 01:02.812
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:02.813 --> 01:05.940
<i>All the love that you felt...</i>

01:05.941 --> 01:12.947
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:12.948 --> 01:16.534
<i>All the memories you shared...</i>

01:16.535 --> 01:23.709
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:24.794 --> 01:26.461
As much as I may try,

01:26.462 --> 01:29.672
I don't think words
will ever be enough.

01:29.673 --> 01:36.054
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:36.055 --> 01:38.056
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

01:38.057 --> 01:41.184
- World without Superman?
Never thought I'd see the day.

01:41.185 --> 01:43.478
- I know he was more
than just an asset to you, Sam.

01:43.479 --> 01:45.021
I'm sorry.
- Appreciate that.

01:45.022 --> 01:47.398
But we need to discuss
how to proceed.

01:47.399 --> 01:49.692
With that monster
still out there and Luthor

01:49.693 --> 01:52.529
pulling its strings,
we don't have much time.

01:52.530 --> 01:54.030
- Got a fallback plan?

01:54.031 --> 01:56.533
- John Henry Irons
and his daughter, Natalie--

01:56.534 --> 02:00.036
I think they'd be more useful
here instead of Metropolis.

02:00.037 --> 02:01.162
Full access, top clearance.

02:01.163 --> 02:03.206
- Done.
Anything else?

02:03.207 --> 02:05.041
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:05.042 --> 02:09.212
- The serum Bruno Mannheim
made to save his wife,

02:09.213 --> 02:12.549
it brought the other Superman
back to life.

02:12.550 --> 02:14.384
You acquired some, correct?

02:14.385 --> 02:17.220
- A vial's worth, yes.

02:17.221 --> 02:19.597
- I need it.

02:19.598 --> 02:22.058
- Does this have anything to do
with Luthor's monster?

02:22.059 --> 02:25.353
- All due respect, not sure
you've earned the privilege.

02:25.354 --> 02:27.397
- How many times are we
going to discuss this, Sam?

02:27.398 --> 02:29.274
- It was a breach of trust.

02:29.275 --> 02:31.109
- We needed a sample
of Superman's blood

02:31.110 --> 02:32.861
in order to save his life.

02:32.862 --> 02:35.363
- And you didn't tell me.
- You were in the hospital.

02:35.364 --> 02:38.575
- I still should have known!
I was his handler!

02:38.576 --> 02:40.577
- You know, there was
a time when you trusted

02:40.578 --> 02:42.745
the DOD more than Superman.

02:42.746 --> 02:45.957
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:45.958 --> 02:49.043
- Help me regain that trust.

02:49.044 --> 02:52.046
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:52.047 --> 02:55.425
- I'll have the serum
sent to your office.

02:55.426 --> 02:58.219
But under no circumstance
are you to use it

02:58.220 --> 03:00.138
unless you tell me
what it's for.

03:00.139 --> 03:02.098
Are we clear?

03:02.099 --> 03:03.766
- Crystal.

03:03.767 --> 03:10.900
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:12.693 --> 03:15.778
Sorry to keep you waiting, pumpkin.

03:15.779 --> 03:17.947
Ever since that alien
showed up,

03:17.948 --> 03:22.744
things around here have been
rowdier than a $10 rodeo.

03:22.745 --> 03:24.787
- Well, actually, sir,
that's--

03:24.788 --> 03:27.123
that's why we're here,
to discuss

03:27.124 --> 03:29.000
S-S-Superman.

03:29.001 --> 03:30.627
- Thought you were here
on boyfriend duty,

03:30.628 --> 03:32.629
not cub reporting.

03:32.630 --> 03:34.923
- [chuckles]
Well, actually--

03:34.924 --> 03:36.674
- There's something
Clark and I want

03:36.675 --> 03:39.802
to tell you about Superman.

03:39.803 --> 03:42.389
- Feel obligated
to share, really.

03:44.516 --> 03:46.476
- You find out where he's from?

03:46.477 --> 03:49.270
- You're never
gonna believe it.

03:49.271 --> 03:50.480
Smallville.

03:50.481 --> 03:52.399
- Smallville?

03:54.902 --> 03:56.152
Isn't that where you grew up?

03:56.153 --> 03:57.445
- Yes, sir.

03:57.446 --> 04:00.198
It--it is.
[chuckles]

04:00.199 --> 04:01.866
- Did you know him?

04:01.867 --> 04:04.036
- You could say that.

04:05.704 --> 04:09.123
- Something
I'm not getting here.

04:09.124 --> 04:10.751
- Sir, I--

04:12.211 --> 04:14.379
I'm him.

04:14.380 --> 04:16.839
Superman, he's--I'm me.

04:16.840 --> 04:20.009
He--we're the same person.
[chuckles]

04:20.010 --> 04:24.639
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:24.640 --> 04:28.017
- No offense, son, but...
[laughs]

04:28.018 --> 04:29.644
Come on.

04:29.645 --> 04:32.021
- OK.
[chuckles]

04:32.022 --> 04:39.113
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:01.802 --> 05:03.804
Tada.

05:05.848 --> 05:07.474
- I'll be damned.

05:08.642 --> 05:10.435
<i>- OK, you're not
gonna believe this,</i>

05:10.436 --> 05:14.481
but these eggless pancakes
may be just as good as yours.

05:15.315 --> 05:17.066
Dad, you got to stop
watching that.

05:17.067 --> 05:19.277
- We should have
helped Clark.

05:19.278 --> 05:22.238
- He told us not to.
- Doesn't matter.

05:22.239 --> 05:23.698
He would have helped us.

05:23.699 --> 05:25.867
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:25.868 --> 05:27.243
[sighs]

05:27.244 --> 05:30.580
- I feel so bad
for Jon and Jordan.

05:30.581 --> 05:33.708
Their dad just died.

05:33.709 --> 05:36.586
- No one should ever have
to lose a parent like that.

05:36.587 --> 05:39.922
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:39.923 --> 05:42.592
[sighs]

05:42.593 --> 05:44.719
- What?

05:44.720 --> 05:46.429
- Sam called.

05:46.430 --> 05:47.597
- And?

05:47.598 --> 05:51.100
- He wants us at the DOD
full-time.

05:51.101 --> 05:53.561
- Wait, so no Metropolis?

05:53.562 --> 05:55.271
- And no Steelworks.

05:55.272 --> 05:56.773
- Which means no DOD school.

05:56.774 --> 05:59.275
- Doesn't mean forever, just...

05:59.276 --> 06:02.779
not in the immediate future.

06:02.780 --> 06:04.572
I know this isn't
what either of us wanted,

06:04.573 --> 06:08.284
but this is the new reality
we're facing.

06:08.285 --> 06:09.994
The world's
without its protector.

06:09.995 --> 06:13.081
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:13.082 --> 06:14.457
- When does Grandpa
need to know?

06:14.458 --> 06:16.084
- End of day.

06:16.085 --> 06:23.217
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:28.722 --> 06:31.849
- [snarling]

06:31.850 --> 06:36.854
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:36.855 --> 06:38.689
[roars]

06:38.690 --> 06:43.277
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:43.278 --> 06:44.696
- [gasps]

06:46.406 --> 06:48.825
- Mom!

06:48.826 --> 06:50.493
You published the article
about dad dying?

06:50.494 --> 06:53.204
- About Superman dying.

06:53.205 --> 06:54.831
The world needs to know.

06:54.832 --> 06:56.457
People have to understand
that Superman

06:56.458 --> 06:58.209
won't be there
to save them anymore.

06:58.210 --> 07:02.839
- Yeah, well, he would be
if someone had listened.

07:02.840 --> 07:04.298
- Jonathan!

07:04.299 --> 07:05.299
- You know it's true.

07:05.300 --> 07:07.718
- Jonathan!

07:07.719 --> 07:09.011
[door slams]

07:09.012 --> 07:12.306
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:12.307 --> 07:13.683
Honey, he didn't mean that.

07:13.684 --> 07:15.852
- Yeah, he did.

07:15.853 --> 07:22.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:24.736 --> 07:26.696
[whooshing]

07:26.697 --> 07:28.197
Dude, I was just
trying to save him.

07:28.198 --> 07:30.408
I'm so sorry.
- I know, all right?

07:30.409 --> 07:31.701
- Look, you have to forgive me.

07:31.702 --> 07:33.244
- Jordan, I'm not blaming you.

07:33.245 --> 07:34.871
Just leave, please.
- You have to forgive me.

07:34.872 --> 07:36.414
- Please--
- I was just--

07:36.415 --> 07:38.416
- Please, will you just
shut up for once

07:38.417 --> 07:40.168
in your stupid life?

07:40.169 --> 07:42.211
I'm so sick of your crap.

07:42.212 --> 07:44.172
Ever since you got powers,
all you've done

07:44.173 --> 07:46.924
is bitch about how hard
everything is!

07:46.925 --> 07:49.177
And you keep saying that you're
trying to do what's right,

07:49.178 --> 07:50.553
but you never do.

07:50.554 --> 07:52.555
You weren't trying to save Dad.

07:52.556 --> 07:56.559
You were trying to be a hero,
and now Dad's dead!

07:56.560 --> 08:01.272
My dad is dead, and I never
get to see him again!

08:01.273 --> 08:04.525
[items clattering]

08:04.526 --> 08:06.527
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:06.528 --> 08:07.778
[grunting]

08:07.779 --> 08:09.197
Ah!

08:09.198 --> 08:15.578
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:15.579 --> 08:19.081
[sobbing]

08:19.082 --> 08:25.087
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:25.088 --> 08:27.381
<i>[high-pitched warbling]</i>

08:27.382 --> 08:29.884
<i>[sirens wailing]</i>

08:29.885 --> 08:37.017
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:41.021 --> 08:42.939
[gasps]

08:42.940 --> 08:45.274
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:45.275 --> 08:46.817
What the hell?

08:46.818 --> 08:51.781
<i>♪ ♪</i>

08:51.782 --> 08:52.782
- Dude.

08:52.783 --> 08:59.915
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:03.210 --> 09:05.586
You got powers.

09:05.587 --> 09:08.297
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:08.298 --> 09:09.549
- Yes.

09:13.345 --> 09:16.556
[whooshing]

09:22.062 --> 09:24.146
- I can't believe
he's flying already.

09:24.147 --> 09:26.524
- Yeah, well, he's a natural.
- This isn't a contest.

09:26.525 --> 09:28.651
Your brother's been waiting
a long time to get his powers,

09:28.652 --> 09:29.944
even if he hasn't said it.

09:29.945 --> 09:31.028
[whooshing]

09:31.029 --> 09:32.321
- Whoo!

09:32.322 --> 09:35.324
Metropolis, New Carthage,

09:35.325 --> 09:37.244
San Francisco.

09:39.079 --> 09:41.497
- OK, you can fly.
Can you do anything else?

09:41.498 --> 09:44.166
- Yeah, I mean, pretty much
everything Dad could.

09:44.167 --> 09:45.793
- That's not possible.

09:45.794 --> 09:47.503
- Well, I've done heat vision
and ice breath.

09:47.504 --> 09:49.797
Plus, I'm, like,
1,000 times stronger.

09:49.798 --> 09:51.132
Oh, and I even heard
Mr. Cushing

09:51.133 --> 09:52.842
getting Chrissy some new car.

09:52.843 --> 09:54.051
Sounded like a minivan.

09:54.052 --> 09:56.387
- For his sake, I hope not.

09:56.388 --> 09:58.848
- Well, thank God
Jon got powers, right?

09:58.849 --> 10:00.474
We can all rest easy now.
- Jordan.

10:00.475 --> 10:02.310
- What's your problem?

10:02.311 --> 10:03.645
- I'm just saying
what everyone's thinking.

10:05.939 --> 10:08.691
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

10:08.692 --> 10:11.027
Mom, I'm--I'm sorry.

10:11.028 --> 10:16.240
- This isn't your fault.
It's just bad timing.

10:16.241 --> 10:18.367
- Is it, though?

10:18.368 --> 10:20.828
I mean, with Dad
not around,

10:20.829 --> 10:23.372
maybe this happened
for a reason.

10:23.373 --> 10:26.208
- If you're implying
this is destiny somehow--

10:26.209 --> 10:28.419
- I'm not trying to scare you.

10:28.420 --> 10:31.255
I just--I just want to help.

10:31.256 --> 10:34.050
Really, that's it.

10:34.051 --> 10:36.052
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:36.053 --> 10:38.220
- I need to talk
to your grandfather.

10:38.221 --> 10:40.514
<i>- I really wasn't
expecting all this.</i>

10:40.515 --> 10:43.100
- This is what
normal people do, right?

10:43.101 --> 10:45.353
They go out in nature.

10:45.354 --> 10:47.730
They--they have picnics.

10:47.731 --> 10:49.065
- No, it's sweet.

10:49.066 --> 10:52.026
Thank you.

10:52.027 --> 10:53.778
- You know...[sighs]

10:53.779 --> 10:55.237
We don't have
to take Lane's offer.

10:55.238 --> 10:56.614
- I know.

10:56.615 --> 10:58.240
- You'd have to quit school.

10:58.241 --> 11:00.117
I'd probably have
to close up shop.

11:00.118 --> 11:01.535
- Yeah.

11:01.536 --> 11:04.413
- I'm sure he could find
someone else.

11:04.414 --> 11:06.749
- No, he can't.

11:06.750 --> 11:09.251
It's the truth,
and we both know it.

11:09.252 --> 11:11.420
There is no one else.

11:11.421 --> 11:12.963
It's just us.

11:12.964 --> 11:15.091
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:15.092 --> 11:18.260
- I just wanted you
to have a normal life.

11:18.261 --> 11:20.763
- [laughs] Yeah, I'm
pretty sure that ship sailed

11:20.764 --> 11:23.391
when evil Superman
destroyed our world.

11:23.392 --> 11:25.893
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:25.894 --> 11:28.062
Dad, I went to school.

11:28.063 --> 11:31.982
You know, I made friends.
I--I fell in love.

11:31.983 --> 11:33.818
- Matteo's a good kid.

11:33.819 --> 11:38.489
- And he's a part
of this world, which I love.

11:38.490 --> 11:41.409
Last time, we didn't get
to fight to save our world.

11:41.410 --> 11:43.619
This time, we do.

11:43.620 --> 11:45.788
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:45.789 --> 11:48.165
- That thing killed Superman.

11:48.166 --> 11:51.961
Might kill us too.

11:51.962 --> 11:55.798
- Yeah, maybe.

11:55.799 --> 11:58.634
But if we can't stop it,
who can?

11:58.635 --> 12:02.805
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:02.806 --> 12:05.975
- Every day, you remind me
more of your mother.

12:05.976 --> 12:10.855
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:10.856 --> 12:12.106
- I miss her.

12:12.107 --> 12:14.108
- Me too.

12:14.109 --> 12:17.070
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:22.033 --> 12:24.118
- Saw the article.

12:24.119 --> 12:25.703
Guess everyone knows
we're living in a world

12:25.704 --> 12:26.954
without Superman now.

12:26.955 --> 12:28.122
God help us all.

12:28.123 --> 12:30.250
- It was the right thing to do.

12:33.795 --> 12:36.089
- Kills me to see you
like this.

12:39.092 --> 12:41.051
You anywhere near OK?

12:41.052 --> 12:45.639
- No, but I'm trying to keep
it together for the boys.

12:45.640 --> 12:47.183
- It's a hard thing,
losing your old man,

12:47.184 --> 12:49.393
especially at that age.

12:49.394 --> 12:52.354
- [clears throat]
Listen...

12:52.355 --> 12:55.150
there's something I have
to tell you about Jonathan.

12:56.985 --> 12:59.028
He got powers.

12:59.029 --> 13:01.322
- I'll be damned.

13:01.323 --> 13:04.867
[laughs] Which ones?

13:04.868 --> 13:06.702
- All of them.

13:06.703 --> 13:08.537
- All of them?

13:08.538 --> 13:11.081
Well, if this doesn't
feel like destiny

13:11.082 --> 13:13.250
rapping its hairy knuckles
on the front door.

13:13.251 --> 13:16.045
- Dad.
- Kid's a born leader,

13:16.046 --> 13:19.048
even been training
to be a fireman.

13:19.049 --> 13:22.259
- He is 16 years old,
and he just lost his father.

13:22.260 --> 13:24.720
He is not ready
to save the world.

13:24.721 --> 13:26.222
- What's Jon got
to say about it?

13:26.223 --> 13:29.558
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:29.559 --> 13:31.894
- He just wants to help.

13:31.895 --> 13:35.189
- Look, if you bring Jon
into the DOD,

13:35.190 --> 13:37.066
we can get him geared up,
train him,

13:37.067 --> 13:38.567
build a team for him.

13:38.568 --> 13:40.069
In my personal opinion,

13:40.070 --> 13:41.862
that's the best course
of action.

13:41.863 --> 13:44.281
I think he's more than capable.

13:44.282 --> 13:47.201
But I didn't tell you
when I was training Jordan.

13:47.202 --> 13:48.702
I won't do that again.

13:48.703 --> 13:49.870
You're his mother.

13:49.871 --> 13:52.248
Whatever choice you make,

13:52.249 --> 13:55.084
I promise I'll respect that.

13:55.085 --> 14:02.217
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:03.343 --> 14:04.593
[knock at door]

14:04.594 --> 14:06.971
- General,
do you have a minute?

14:06.972 --> 14:08.264
- Close that door, will you?

14:08.265 --> 14:09.640
- Yeah.

14:09.641 --> 14:10.975
- Heh!

14:10.976 --> 14:12.434
I've been hoping you'd drop by.

14:12.435 --> 14:14.103
- Oh.

14:14.104 --> 14:16.730
- You finally ready to talk
about working for the DOD?

14:16.731 --> 14:19.817
- Actually, I'm still
thinking that over.

14:19.818 --> 14:22.653
- Then why are you here?

14:22.654 --> 14:26.782
- Well, sir, I--

14:26.783 --> 14:29.827
I'd like to formally ask you
for Lois' hand in marriage.

14:29.828 --> 14:32.121
- Oh, damn it, son.

14:32.122 --> 14:33.789
That's a terrible idea!

14:33.790 --> 14:36.084
- [laughs]

14:37.377 --> 14:40.754
Well, sir, I--

14:40.755 --> 14:42.423
I'm in love with your daughter.

14:42.424 --> 14:43.966
I--I want to spend the rest
of my life with her.

14:43.967 --> 14:46.302
- Then you need to remedy that!

14:46.303 --> 14:48.470
'Cause married life
isn't in the cards for you.

14:48.471 --> 14:50.014
- General.

14:50.015 --> 14:52.308
- You and I are this world's
last line of defense.

14:52.309 --> 14:55.144
We don't get to sign up for
the friends and family program.

14:55.145 --> 14:56.854
- With all due respect, sir,
you're wrong.

14:56.855 --> 14:58.981
I need Lois.

14:58.982 --> 15:01.317
- It'll fade.

15:01.318 --> 15:02.526
Love always does.

15:02.527 --> 15:03.819
- Yeah, but I do love her.

15:03.820 --> 15:05.696
- So do I.

15:05.697 --> 15:07.781
More than you will
ever understand.

15:07.782 --> 15:10.618
And I would do anything
to protect Lois.

15:10.619 --> 15:11.827
- As would I.

15:11.828 --> 15:13.329
- That were true,
you'd walk away!

15:13.330 --> 15:15.331
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:15.332 --> 15:18.375
[sighs]

15:18.376 --> 15:21.837
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:21.838 --> 15:25.299
Lois doesn't deserve
this kind of life.

15:25.300 --> 15:28.218
She went through hell already
with her mother.

15:28.219 --> 15:29.845
- I will never leave her.

15:29.846 --> 15:32.014
- Not intentionally.

15:32.015 --> 15:34.141
But you don't know
what's out there,

15:34.142 --> 15:37.227
the evil
that's coming for you.

15:37.228 --> 15:40.564
You may not have faced much of
a threat yet, but believe me,

15:40.565 --> 15:42.232
you will.

15:42.233 --> 15:44.026
And when that day comes,

15:44.027 --> 15:46.153
the worst-case scenario
happens.

15:46.154 --> 15:47.863
She's the one
who's gonna feel that pain

15:47.864 --> 15:49.198
for the rest of her life.

15:49.199 --> 15:52.409
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:52.410 --> 15:55.579
- I came here to ask
for your blessing.

15:55.580 --> 15:57.331
But I want to be clear--

15:57.332 --> 16:00.376
I do intend
to marry your daughter.

16:00.377 --> 16:03.712
- Then why even bother asking?

16:03.713 --> 16:06.215
- Because I'd like for you
to be a part of our family.

16:06.216 --> 16:08.509
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:08.510 --> 16:14.390
- Well, you do
what you have to, son.

16:14.391 --> 16:16.058
You know where I stand.

16:16.059 --> 16:22.816
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:38.039 --> 16:41.208
- And now it's eating
the entrails.

16:41.209 --> 16:43.419
You can't be bothered to visit
the board in Metropolis,

16:43.420 --> 16:45.921
but you'll drop by
to feed that?

16:45.922 --> 16:49.299
- The difference is,
I like him.

16:49.300 --> 16:51.802
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:51.803 --> 16:53.804
- I can see the appeal.

16:53.805 --> 16:56.765
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:56.766 --> 16:58.642
- [growls]

16:58.643 --> 17:00.561
- Where are we
with General Lane?

17:00.562 --> 17:01.937
- Our asset is in place,

17:01.938 --> 17:03.105
and the carrot
has been presented.

17:03.106 --> 17:04.440
- Loved ones?

17:04.441 --> 17:06.775
- Tend to get
the biggest bites.

17:06.776 --> 17:08.610
- We have one shot at this.

17:08.611 --> 17:11.155
- If this doesn't work,
nothing will get Lane to talk.

17:11.156 --> 17:13.115
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:13.116 --> 17:14.992
Do you want me
to give the go-ahead?

17:14.993 --> 17:16.994
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:16.995 --> 17:17.995
- Do it.

17:17.996 --> 17:19.788
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:19.789 --> 17:24.126
- [growls]

17:24.127 --> 17:27.213
[roaring]

17:33.094 --> 17:36.013
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:36.014 --> 17:39.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:39.350 --> 17:42.102
- [sniffs, sighs]

17:42.103 --> 17:44.856
- What are you doing?
- This is insane.

17:46.107 --> 17:48.484
How things look,
how they sound,

17:48.485 --> 17:51.987
how they smell--
it's so intense.

17:51.988 --> 17:55.157
- Careful.
That one can backfire on you.

17:55.158 --> 17:59.036
Your father hated
Limburger cheese.

17:59.037 --> 18:00.329
- [chuckles]

18:00.330 --> 18:02.831
- Have a seat, honey.

18:02.832 --> 18:05.542
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:05.543 --> 18:08.003
- What did Grandpa say?

18:08.004 --> 18:10.464
- There was never any doubt.

18:10.465 --> 18:12.216
He's always had
a soft spot for you.

18:12.217 --> 18:14.343
- [chuckles]
Probably 'cause of football.

18:14.344 --> 18:16.178
- It's more than that.

18:16.179 --> 18:20.349
- OK, so what do you think?

18:20.350 --> 18:23.519
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:23.520 --> 18:26.021
- What I think
is that your father and I

18:26.022 --> 18:30.526
made a lot of mistakes when it
came to you boys and powers.

18:30.527 --> 18:32.069
We should have told you
years ago

18:32.070 --> 18:33.737
who your father really was,

18:33.738 --> 18:36.031
taught about your heritage,

18:36.032 --> 18:39.576
and prepped you
for what to expect

18:39.577 --> 18:43.330
if your powers manifested.

18:43.331 --> 18:45.833
There are so many things
I would have done differently.

18:45.834 --> 18:48.710
- Doesn't every parent
say that at some point?

18:48.711 --> 18:51.505
- Probably, but it doesn't
make me worry any less.

18:51.506 --> 18:54.049
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:54.050 --> 18:56.426
- I'm not asking
for some superhero suit

18:56.427 --> 19:01.557
and to instantly be
who Dad was.

19:01.558 --> 19:04.059
I got a lot to learn.

19:04.060 --> 19:07.396
And I want to learn it.

19:07.397 --> 19:13.235
But being able
to do what I can now,

19:13.236 --> 19:16.405
if I can save one family
from losing someone they love

19:16.406 --> 19:19.867
like we lost Dad,

19:19.868 --> 19:21.368
then I have to.

19:21.369 --> 19:24.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:24.747 --> 19:26.915
- OK.
- Really?

19:26.916 --> 19:29.126
- I'll tell your grandfather
we're coming.

19:29.127 --> 19:31.378
Go get your stuff.
- OK.

19:31.379 --> 19:36.509
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:46.311 --> 19:50.105
Man, I'm really sorry
about what I said before.

19:50.106 --> 19:51.106
I didn't mean it.

19:51.107 --> 19:52.608
- Yeah, you did.

19:52.609 --> 19:54.776
- Jordan.

19:54.777 --> 19:57.571
- Hey, man,
have fun at the DOD.

19:57.572 --> 19:59.615
- I thought one of the rules
of having super-hearing

19:59.616 --> 20:02.743
was that we don't
eavesdrop on each other.

20:02.744 --> 20:04.453
- Easier said than done.

20:04.454 --> 20:11.544
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:13.254 --> 20:14.630
- You sure
you don't want to come?

20:14.631 --> 20:17.633
- Nah, man.
Good luck.

20:17.634 --> 20:19.134
- OK.

20:19.135 --> 20:25.349
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:25.350 --> 20:29.186
I know the dynamic here
has changed considerably,

20:29.187 --> 20:33.023
but we'll give you the same
courtesy Superman enjoyed--

20:33.024 --> 20:34.441
best of the best
on your comms team

20:34.442 --> 20:36.318
while you're in the field...
- Sam.

20:36.319 --> 20:38.820
- Full access to our
world-class research labs...

20:38.821 --> 20:40.489
- Grandpa.

20:40.490 --> 20:42.950
- Tech updates to your suits
as they become available.

20:42.951 --> 20:45.494
- Sam, stop.

20:45.495 --> 20:46.828
You don't have to sell us.

20:46.829 --> 20:48.830
We know how it works.

20:48.831 --> 20:50.332
- We're in.

20:50.333 --> 20:52.834
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:52.835 --> 20:55.629
- Right, I just want
to make sure we're clear

20:55.630 --> 20:57.798
about what you're
stepping into.

20:57.799 --> 20:59.883
You have any questions
or concerns,

20:59.884 --> 21:02.177
we work them out right now.

21:02.178 --> 21:03.845
Superman and I
didn't always have

21:03.846 --> 21:06.390
the best working relationship.

21:06.391 --> 21:09.726
I don't want that for us,

21:09.727 --> 21:12.521
especially with you, kiddo.

21:12.522 --> 21:15.524
- Hey, all we need to know

21:15.525 --> 21:18.151
is that you got our back.

21:18.152 --> 21:20.862
- I got your back.

21:20.863 --> 21:23.532
[door bangs open]
- Sam.

21:23.533 --> 21:25.867
- John Henry
and Natalie Irons--

21:25.868 --> 21:28.870
or how you'll be known around
here, Steel and Starlight--

21:28.871 --> 21:31.039
I'd like you to meet
General Hardcastle

21:31.040 --> 21:33.041
and Squad K.
This is your new team.

21:33.042 --> 21:35.711
- Welcome.
It's an honor.

21:35.712 --> 21:37.713
This is Jonell Jones.
[phone buzzes]

21:37.714 --> 21:39.339
- Good to meet you.
- Phillip Darnell.

21:39.340 --> 21:40.716
- Hi.
Terry Coffey.

21:40.717 --> 21:42.342
- I'll check back in
with you later.

21:42.343 --> 21:43.760
- Everything OK?

21:43.761 --> 21:45.012
- Getting there.

21:45.013 --> 21:52.145
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:00.153 --> 22:01.903
- [coughs]

22:01.904 --> 22:08.995
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:11.456 --> 22:14.374
<i>[ominous music]</i>

22:14.375 --> 22:19.379
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:19.380 --> 22:21.423
- Afternoon, Superboy.

22:21.424 --> 22:25.219
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:29.515 --> 22:31.725
- Surprised this place
didn't burn down.

22:31.726 --> 22:33.602
[crackling]

22:33.603 --> 22:35.771
You sure you want
to try that again?

22:35.772 --> 22:38.774
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

22:38.775 --> 22:41.610
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:41.611 --> 22:42.944
- What do you want?

22:42.945 --> 22:46.782
- There's something
you need to hear.

22:46.783 --> 22:50.744
I think it'll clarify
some things about your mom.

22:50.745 --> 22:51.953
- I'm good.

22:51.954 --> 22:53.455
- You think she has a favorite?

22:53.456 --> 22:55.916
[phone clicks]

22:55.917 --> 22:56.917
- What?

22:56.918 --> 22:59.252
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:59.253 --> 23:01.838
- You or your brother?

23:01.839 --> 23:04.800
My guess is, she likes to say
she loves you both the same.

23:04.801 --> 23:06.259
- Look, whatever
you're trying to do--

23:06.260 --> 23:09.012
- I told you,
your mother's a liar.

23:09.013 --> 23:10.806
Hear for yourself.

23:10.807 --> 23:12.474
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:12.475 --> 23:14.267
<i>- Your sons are in danger.</i>

23:14.268 --> 23:16.812
<i>If you want Jordan to live,
press 1.</i>

23:16.813 --> 23:19.481
<i>If you want Jonathan to live,
press 2.</i>

23:19.482 --> 23:22.317
<i>You have 10 seconds to choose.</i>

23:22.318 --> 23:25.445
<i>9, 8...
- Stop this! Stop it!</i>

23:25.446 --> 23:26.863
- What--what is this?

23:26.864 --> 23:28.782
- The other day when you were
at the shipyard,

23:28.783 --> 23:29.866
your mom got this call.

23:29.867 --> 23:31.326
- Jon wasn't even in trouble.

23:31.327 --> 23:33.453
- Ah-ah.
Listen.

23:33.454 --> 23:35.705
<i>- 2, 1.
[touch tone beeps]</i>

23:35.706 --> 23:37.833
<i>You have chosen Jonathan.</i>

23:37.834 --> 23:40.877
<i>He's a good boy
and your favorite son.</i>

23:40.878 --> 23:43.463
<i>Thanks for being honest
for once.</i>

23:43.464 --> 23:44.881
<i>Have a nice day.</i>

23:44.882 --> 23:46.466
<i>[line beeping]</i>

23:46.467 --> 23:52.305
<i>♪ ♪</i>

23:52.306 --> 23:53.849
- That isn't real.

23:53.850 --> 23:55.350
- Ask her yourself.

23:55.351 --> 23:57.060
You'll know
if she's telling the truth.

23:57.061 --> 23:58.395
- It doesn't matter.

23:58.396 --> 23:59.688
- Maybe not,

23:59.689 --> 24:03.316
but you have to wonder...

24:03.317 --> 24:06.194
what else has she been
lying to you about?

24:06.195 --> 24:09.906
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:09.907 --> 24:11.408
She'll always pick him.

24:11.409 --> 24:13.994
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:13.995 --> 24:16.496
At least now you know.

24:16.497 --> 24:23.629
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:26.465 --> 24:29.468
[indistinct chatter]

24:31.971 --> 24:33.681
- Can I have a word?

24:37.643 --> 24:38.894
[clears throat, sighs]

24:38.895 --> 24:40.937
Has General Lane
mentioned anything to you

24:40.938 --> 24:42.939
about Bruno Mannheim's serum?

24:42.940 --> 24:44.691
- The stuff he used
on Matteo's mom?

24:44.692 --> 24:46.776
- And on that other Superman.

24:46.777 --> 24:48.570
- Please tell me the DOD
isn't trying to use it.

24:48.571 --> 24:50.906
- We're not.

24:50.907 --> 24:52.741
But I think
General Lane might be.

24:52.742 --> 24:55.076
- For what?

24:55.077 --> 24:56.745
- [sighs]
He wants to make

24:56.746 --> 24:58.246
his own monster
to fight Luthor's.

24:58.247 --> 25:01.917
- I worry if someone
doesn't stop Lane now,

25:01.918 --> 25:05.754
we're gonna have two
of those things to deal with.

25:05.755 --> 25:12.887
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:18.851 --> 25:21.937
- General Lane, we're almost
ready to begin the ceremony.

25:21.938 --> 25:24.773
Congratulations, General.

25:24.774 --> 25:26.651
- Says you, Father.

25:30.363 --> 25:33.949
- You tried your best to get
the general's blessing, Clark.

25:33.950 --> 25:36.576
There's nothing more
you can do.

25:36.577 --> 25:38.787
- It just doesn't feel fair
to Lois.

25:38.788 --> 25:40.455
- Well, maybe not.

25:40.456 --> 25:42.958
But you said it yourself,
she and her father have a...

25:42.959 --> 25:45.794
difficult relationship.

25:45.795 --> 25:48.463
- I was kind of hoping
this would help with that.

25:48.464 --> 25:50.465
- Always wanting
to be the hero, huh?

25:50.466 --> 25:51.925
- No, no.

25:51.926 --> 25:53.468
It just doesn't feel
entirely right

25:53.469 --> 25:54.928
getting married
without him on board.

25:54.929 --> 25:56.137
That's all.

25:56.138 --> 25:58.265
- OK, then let me ask you this.

25:58.266 --> 26:00.642
Do you love Lois?

26:00.643 --> 26:02.143
- Of course.

26:02.144 --> 26:04.980
- Do you want to start
a family with her?

26:04.981 --> 26:07.023
- More than anything.

26:07.024 --> 26:09.526
- Clark, you're gonna be
a great husband

26:09.527 --> 26:11.194
and a terrific father.

26:11.195 --> 26:14.698
And if the general
can't see that, that's on him.

26:14.699 --> 26:16.950
- Thanks, Mom.

26:16.951 --> 26:19.995
- That's what
I'm here for, honey.

26:19.996 --> 26:26.293
Now, get out there and marry
that wonderful woman.

26:26.294 --> 26:28.461
- General Lane
should be in his office.

26:28.462 --> 26:30.839
- Mom.

26:30.840 --> 26:32.674
- I know where it is.
Thank you.

26:32.675 --> 26:34.093
Hey.

26:35.761 --> 26:37.679
- Dude, what's wrong?

26:37.680 --> 26:39.514
- Did you really choose Jon?

26:39.515 --> 26:41.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:41.851 --> 26:44.060
Luthor played me a tape.

26:44.061 --> 26:45.312
Is it true?

26:45.313 --> 26:47.022
- Jordan, it's not
what you think.

26:47.023 --> 26:49.065
- Both your sons are in danger.

26:49.066 --> 26:51.526
You can only choose one,
and you chose your favorite.

26:51.527 --> 26:54.571
- That's not true.
- Don't lie to me.

26:54.572 --> 26:56.489
You chose him.
I heard you.

26:56.490 --> 26:58.325
- Mom, what's he talking about?

26:58.326 --> 27:00.035
- Honey, there was no time.

27:00.036 --> 27:01.494
I did not know
what was happening.

27:01.495 --> 27:03.913
And you were the one
with powers.

27:03.914 --> 27:06.333
- Luthor knew I had powers.

27:06.334 --> 27:07.417
He wasn't even in trouble.

27:07.418 --> 27:08.918
I was the one being attacked!

27:08.919 --> 27:10.503
- Sweetie, I didn't know that.

27:10.504 --> 27:11.588
- Would it have even mattered?

27:11.589 --> 27:13.089
- Of course it would have.

27:13.090 --> 27:17.218
I have always
loved you both the same.

27:17.219 --> 27:18.553
- He said you'd say that.

27:18.554 --> 27:20.221
- Lex Luthor is a liar.

27:20.222 --> 27:22.057
- And you're not?

27:22.058 --> 27:24.225
You sent him to prison for
a crime he didn't even commit.

27:24.226 --> 27:27.062
- Don't you ever
say that to me again!

27:27.063 --> 27:28.563
Not ever!

27:28.564 --> 27:33.068
That man killed your father.

27:33.069 --> 27:35.570
Jordan, you need to understand,

27:35.571 --> 27:39.908
Lex Luthor is using you
to hurt me.

27:39.909 --> 27:42.452
- Right.

27:42.453 --> 27:44.537
'Cause I'm so weak.

27:44.538 --> 27:46.748
- Jordan.
[whooshing]

27:46.749 --> 27:52.129
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:55.841 --> 27:58.051
- Lois, is that you?

27:58.052 --> 27:59.719
Jones.

27:59.720 --> 28:01.304
- Sorry, General.

28:01.305 --> 28:04.557
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:04.558 --> 28:06.768
<i>- I know my daughter
came to see you, General.</i>

28:06.769 --> 28:08.436
<i>Now you're gonna tell me
where to find her.</i>

28:08.437 --> 28:09.729
- Like hell I am.

28:09.730 --> 28:10.772
- He's threatening my family.

28:10.773 --> 28:12.107
- Damn it, Jones.

28:12.108 --> 28:13.900
I gave that young lady my word.

28:13.901 --> 28:15.443
We cannot give in to threats.

28:15.444 --> 28:17.112
<i>- Either you give me
Elizabeth now,</i>

28:17.113 --> 28:19.322
<i>or I can send something
that doesn't need a gun.</i>

28:19.323 --> 28:21.116
- We got to get people
out of here.

28:21.117 --> 28:23.243
- You didn't say
anything about that.

28:23.244 --> 28:25.286
[both grunting]

28:25.287 --> 28:28.456
[gunshot]
- [groaning]

28:28.457 --> 28:30.166
- So sorry, sir.

28:30.167 --> 28:32.335
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:32.336 --> 28:33.586
[grunts]

28:33.587 --> 28:36.339
[breathing heavily]

28:36.340 --> 28:39.718
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:44.390 --> 28:47.308
<i>[heartbeat thumping]</i>
- [breathing shallowly]

28:47.309 --> 28:50.311
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

28:50.312 --> 28:57.403
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:13.252 --> 29:16.004
[gasps]

29:16.005 --> 29:21.384
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:21.385 --> 29:23.678
- Sam, Sam!

29:23.679 --> 29:27.056
- Grandpa.
My God, what happened?

29:27.057 --> 29:28.516
- What did you do?

29:28.517 --> 29:30.685
- Go tell everyone
to get the hell out of here.

29:30.686 --> 29:32.395
Luthor's sending
that thing for me.

29:32.396 --> 29:34.689
Go, please.

29:34.690 --> 29:37.859
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:37.860 --> 29:39.486
Give these to Lois.

29:39.487 --> 29:40.862
- Sam.

29:40.863 --> 29:44.032
- You need to stop it.

29:44.033 --> 29:45.909
Suit up, John.

29:45.910 --> 29:50.205
And then you need to promise me
you'll do exactly what I say.

29:50.206 --> 29:52.332
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:52.333 --> 29:53.875
<i>- You need to evacuate now.</i>

29:53.876 --> 29:55.043
- Where is it?

29:55.044 --> 29:57.045
- Nothing yet, ma'am.

29:57.046 --> 29:58.588
- General, kryptonite
has been detected

29:58.589 --> 30:01.382
moving in the atmosphere.

30:01.383 --> 30:03.218
- 20 seconds out
and approaching fast.

30:03.219 --> 30:04.719
- Time to move.

30:04.720 --> 30:07.055
[indistinct chatter]

30:07.056 --> 30:08.723
- Dad?
<i>- Be right there.</i>

30:08.724 --> 30:10.183
[whooshing]

30:10.184 --> 30:12.393
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:12.394 --> 30:15.396
[indistinct yelling]

30:15.397 --> 30:22.321
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:29.495 --> 30:31.287
<i>- 15 seconds, Natalie.</i>

30:31.288 --> 30:32.539
- You ready, Bug?

30:32.540 --> 30:33.581
- We got this, Dad.

30:33.582 --> 30:35.625
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:35.626 --> 30:37.043
<i>- 8 seconds.</i>

30:37.044 --> 30:39.754
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:39.755 --> 30:40.922
- Oh, my God.

30:40.923 --> 30:42.549
- Split formation.

30:42.550 --> 30:43.883
Use all the yellow
solar flares,

30:43.884 --> 30:45.301
all of them at once.

30:45.302 --> 30:46.427
Lock on target.

30:46.428 --> 30:48.429
- Got it.
<i>- 4 seconds.</i>

30:48.430 --> 30:51.099
- Don't hold back.
<i>- 3 seconds.</i>

30:51.100 --> 30:52.809
<i>2 seconds.</i>

30:52.810 --> 30:54.811
<i>1 second.</i>

30:54.812 --> 30:58.439
[explosion]

30:58.440 --> 30:59.567
- [grunts]

31:02.319 --> 31:04.445
[explosion]

31:04.446 --> 31:11.537
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:13.998 --> 31:16.624
- Dad!
- [computer trilling]

31:16.625 --> 31:20.628
- [roars]

31:20.629 --> 31:27.219
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:35.227 --> 31:38.021
[indistinct yelling]

31:38.022 --> 31:44.403
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:46.739 --> 31:47.780
[roars]

31:47.781 --> 31:49.699
- Engage!

31:49.700 --> 31:52.493
- Cease fire!

31:52.494 --> 31:54.495
- Dad?

31:54.496 --> 31:56.873
- Oh, pumpkin, it's OK.
It's OK.

31:56.874 --> 31:58.333
You got to trust me.

31:58.334 --> 32:00.793
- [snarling]

32:00.794 --> 32:04.631
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:04.632 --> 32:07.842
- I can't convince you
to walk away, can I?

32:07.843 --> 32:12.138
- Dad, I am literally
about to exchange my vows.

32:12.139 --> 32:14.515
I think it's time to put
this idea to rest, don't you?

32:14.516 --> 32:19.520
- My concern only comes
from a place of love.

32:19.521 --> 32:21.981
I just didn't want you
to make the same mistakes

32:21.982 --> 32:23.316
your mother and I made.

32:23.317 --> 32:26.235
- We are nothing
like you and Mom.

32:26.236 --> 32:29.405
- Stubborn, driven,
career-oriented

32:29.406 --> 32:32.033
young woman
marries a service-minded,

32:32.034 --> 32:34.535
dutiful, workaholic young man?

32:34.536 --> 32:38.081
It's a recipe for disaster.

32:38.082 --> 32:41.209
Believe me.

32:41.210 --> 32:43.211
Especially with kids.

32:43.212 --> 32:46.673
- We are entering this marriage
with our eyes wide open.

32:46.674 --> 32:51.386
- I'm just saying, you fell
in love with Clark Kent,

32:51.387 --> 32:54.055
but you're marrying Superman.

32:54.056 --> 32:58.935
- And they both make me happier
than I have ever been.

32:58.936 --> 33:01.938
Please, Dad, trust me.

33:01.939 --> 33:03.940
Trust in us.

33:03.941 --> 33:10.656
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:11.615 --> 33:13.908
- OK, pumpkin.

33:13.909 --> 33:16.035
I trust you.

33:16.036 --> 33:17.954
I still have reservations.

33:17.955 --> 33:21.290
I will for a long time.

33:21.291 --> 33:25.712
But I see
how much you love him.

33:25.713 --> 33:28.047
I know how much he loves you.

33:28.048 --> 33:30.550
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:30.551 --> 33:33.469
So yeah.
[laughs]

33:33.470 --> 33:36.097
Yes, you have my blessing.

33:36.098 --> 33:38.474
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:38.475 --> 33:40.643
- Thanks, Daddy.

33:40.644 --> 33:43.771
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:43.772 --> 33:47.108
- You look so beautiful.

33:47.109 --> 33:50.069
[Wagner's "Bridal Chorus"
playing on piano]

33:50.070 --> 33:52.238
I guess it's time.

33:52.239 --> 33:59.371
♪ ♪

34:05.878 --> 34:08.796
- I know how scary
this is for you.

34:08.797 --> 34:11.174
But it means the world to me.

34:11.175 --> 34:13.843
♪ ♪

34:13.844 --> 34:17.764
- I'll always be brave
for you, pumpkin.

34:17.765 --> 34:19.474
Always.

34:19.475 --> 34:22.143
♪ ♪

34:22.144 --> 34:25.313
You know my answer, Luthor.

34:25.314 --> 34:27.315
<i>- Tell me where Elizabeth is.</i>

34:27.316 --> 34:29.317
- I promised to protect her.

34:29.318 --> 34:30.359
<i>- Where is she?</i>

34:30.360 --> 34:31.652
- I gave her my word.

34:31.653 --> 34:32.862
<i>- Tell me now!</i>

34:32.863 --> 34:37.700
- I promised her I'd be brave.

34:37.701 --> 34:41.454
<i>- Last chance, General.</i>

34:41.455 --> 34:43.372
- Stand down.
- Daddy, what are you doing?

34:43.373 --> 34:45.792
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:45.793 --> 34:49.712
- You're gonna be OK, pumpkin.

34:49.713 --> 34:50.880
<i>- Do it!</i>

34:50.881 --> 34:52.340
- [grunts]

34:52.341 --> 34:57.678
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:57.679 --> 35:00.181
[bones crack]

35:00.182 --> 35:02.183
- No!

35:02.184 --> 35:04.185
- [roars]

35:04.186 --> 35:11.318
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:26.625 --> 35:29.085
- No, no!

35:29.086 --> 35:30.837
[sobbing]

35:30.838 --> 35:33.214
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

35:33.215 --> 35:36.175
- I need to take Sam's body.
It's what he wanted.

35:36.176 --> 35:38.261
Just go back to the farm.
Nat will explain everything.

35:38.262 --> 35:45.435
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:51.483 --> 35:53.568
- I need your help.

35:53.569 --> 35:55.361
- John Henry Irons.

35:55.362 --> 35:57.113
<i>♪ ♪</i>

35:57.114 --> 35:59.448
- We don't have much time.

35:59.449 --> 36:06.623
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:08.000 --> 36:09.083
- What's going on?

36:09.084 --> 36:15.631
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:15.632 --> 36:18.551
- I'm sorry, sweetie,
but your grandfather--

36:18.552 --> 36:20.303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:20.304 --> 36:21.929
- That thing killed him.

36:21.930 --> 36:26.642
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:26.643 --> 36:31.731
- [sighs]
He died protecting us.

36:31.732 --> 36:32.773
- Actually...

36:32.774 --> 36:35.443
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:35.444 --> 36:37.278
It was more than that.

36:37.279 --> 36:38.446
<i>- We're gonna use
General Lane's heart</i>

36:38.447 --> 36:39.780
<i>to bring back Superman.</i>

36:39.781 --> 36:41.073
- But his heart
will not suffice.

36:41.074 --> 36:42.158
It is from a human.

36:42.159 --> 36:43.743
- Lane injected himself

36:43.744 --> 36:45.286
with a serum containing
Superman's blood.

36:45.287 --> 36:47.580
That blood was flowing
through his heart

36:47.581 --> 36:48.623
right before he died.

36:48.624 --> 36:49.957
- I fear that is not the same.

36:49.958 --> 36:52.960
- It is the closest
we're gonna get.

36:52.961 --> 36:55.463
Help me,
before the serum wears off.

36:55.464 --> 37:00.635
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:00.636 --> 37:02.345
- I don't understand.

37:02.346 --> 37:03.804
Why did he have
to use his own heart?

37:03.805 --> 37:05.473
- Grandpa was searching
for a donor.

37:05.474 --> 37:09.310
But after he got shot,
there wasn't any time.

37:09.311 --> 37:12.271
Nobody else knew about
the plan, so it had to be him.

37:12.272 --> 37:15.107
- So when he went outside,
he knew what was gonna happen.

37:15.108 --> 37:17.360
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:17.361 --> 37:19.487
- How do we know
if it'll even work?

37:19.488 --> 37:20.988
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:20.989 --> 37:22.990
- Grandpa says
we have to have hope.

37:22.991 --> 37:25.117
- There.

37:25.118 --> 37:27.954
The new heart is being
prepared for transfer.

37:27.955 --> 37:29.830
- How long will it take?

37:29.831 --> 37:32.333
- The procedure itself
is not long.

37:32.334 --> 37:35.544
But if Kal is to return,
it will take many days.

37:35.545 --> 37:40.132
And even then, I have concerns.

37:40.133 --> 37:44.053
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:44.054 --> 37:45.513
<i>- There is one more thing.</i>

37:45.514 --> 37:49.684
He made this for you,
right before.

37:49.685 --> 37:56.775
<i>♪ ♪</i>

37:59.277 --> 38:01.028
<i>- Hey, pumpkin.</i>

38:01.029 --> 38:04.198
<i>Sorry to be so rushed here,
but...[sighs]</i>

38:04.199 --> 38:06.867
<i>Looks like my time's
about to run out.</i>

38:06.868 --> 38:11.664
<i>And--and before
that happens, I--</i>

38:11.665 --> 38:14.083
<i>I wanted to tell you...</i>

38:14.084 --> 38:16.919
<i>[laughs]</i>

38:16.920 --> 38:19.255
<i>You're the best thing
that ever happened to me.</i>

38:19.256 --> 38:21.841
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:21.842 --> 38:25.052
<i>I was closed off
and set in my ways.</i>

38:25.053 --> 38:30.057
<i>And you and Clark,</i>

38:30.058 --> 38:36.897
<i>you insisted on making me
part of your family.</i>

38:36.898 --> 38:41.569
<i>And--and that has been
the greatest joy of my life.</i>

38:41.570 --> 38:44.613
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:44.614 --> 38:48.200
<i>Those boys and Nat, I can't--</i>

38:48.201 --> 38:51.120
<i>I can't put into words
how much--</i>

38:51.121 --> 38:52.747
<i>how much I love them.</i>

38:52.748 --> 38:55.291
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:55.292 --> 38:57.877
<i>And you.
[laughs]</i>

38:57.878 --> 39:01.213
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:01.214 --> 39:05.468
<i>You have always been
my North Star.</i>

39:05.469 --> 39:08.262
<i>You made me a better man.</i>

39:08.263 --> 39:12.600
<i>You--you made me a dad.</i>

39:12.601 --> 39:15.936
<i>I'm so, so proud
to be your father.</i>

39:15.937 --> 39:19.732
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:19.733 --> 39:21.317
<i>- We don't have much time,
Sam.</i>

39:21.318 --> 39:23.069
<i>It's almost here.</i>

39:23.070 --> 39:24.945
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:24.946 --> 39:29.283
<i>- Clark, he once told me
he'd always be there for you,</i>

39:29.284 --> 39:32.453
<i>and I--I didn't get it then.</i>

39:32.454 --> 39:34.246
<i>I do now.</i>

39:34.247 --> 39:36.999
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:37.000 --> 39:39.835
<i>He's gonna come back.</i>

39:39.836 --> 39:44.131
<i>And once they get my heart
inside him,</i>

39:44.132 --> 39:47.301
<i>I'll be there, too,</i>

39:47.302 --> 39:50.471
<i>for every beat, ev--</i>

39:50.472 --> 39:53.974
<i>every single beat.</i>

39:53.975 --> 39:56.477
<i>♪ ♪</i>

39:56.478 --> 39:59.105
<i>- Dad?
- Be right there.</i>

39:59.106 --> 40:02.775
<i>- I guess--</i>

40:02.776 --> 40:05.986
<i>I guess this
is goodbye for now.</i>

40:05.987 --> 40:08.531
<i>I love you, pumpkin,</i>

40:08.532 --> 40:10.533
<i>more than you could
possibly know.</i>

40:10.534 --> 40:12.451
- I love you.

40:12.452 --> 40:19.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:19.459 --> 40:21.502
<i>Can you ever truly explain</i>

40:21.503 --> 40:24.338
<i>how much a person
meant to you?</i>

40:24.339 --> 40:28.717
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:28.718 --> 40:31.011
Is it even possible?

40:31.012 --> 40:33.514
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:33.515 --> 40:35.558
All the love that you felt...

40:35.559 --> 40:39.311
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:39.312 --> 40:42.356
All the memories
that you shared,

40:42.357 --> 40:44.024
as much as I may try,

40:44.025 --> 40:46.318
I don't think words
will ever be enough.

40:46.319 --> 40:50.739
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:50.740 --> 40:52.992
But I do know there is
no one else in the world

40:52.993 --> 40:55.369
I would have wanted as my dad.

40:55.370 --> 41:01.876
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:01.877 --> 41:03.878
I love you, Dad.

41:03.879 --> 41:06.881
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:06.882 --> 41:10.176
You were always my hero.

41:10.177 --> 41:17.309
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:33.491 --> 41:36.410
<i>[ominous music]</i>

41:36.411 --> 41:43.501
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:52.510 --> 41:54.595
- [inhales sharply]

41:54.596 --> 41:57.682
<i>[heartbeat thumping]</i>

42:21.373 --> 42:22.874
- Greg, move your head.
